column5: Hi everyone,  I am headed up to Callander Bay in a week and was just wondering how the fishing has been.  I thought that there was a messageboard for the Nip, but for the life of me I can't find it.  So if anyone has been up, has it been HOT or NOT??  thanks in advance  Brian
I think that Nipppy board exploded when the problems at lake simcoe fishing arose.
Here you go:  Lake Nipissing   Tom
Hey thanks Tom, much appreciated.  And Jed, what does that mean? "Becareful how you spend your money"  Thanks again  Brian

Fishings been slow for last couple weeks but Ive heard good things from this past weekend up in callander area, some nice pike being caught at night  n' a couple keeper eyes.  I was up 2 weekends ago, got a few small guys, nothin' to write home about.  plenty of mudpuppys hehe.
